WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:01.950 --> 00:00:03.100
KOH KIM: Whoa, showtime.

00:00:03.100 --> 00:00:04.200
DAN GALPIN: Exactly.

00:00:04.200 --> 00:00:06.750
All right, so I'm Dan Galpin,
and I'm a developer advocate

00:00:06.750 --> 00:00:08.160
with Android Games.

00:00:08.160 --> 00:00:08.780
And with--

00:00:08.780 --> 00:00:09.140
KOH KIM: And I'm--

00:00:09.140 --> 00:00:10.330
DAN GALPIN: With me is--

00:00:10.330 --> 00:00:10.780
KOH KIM: With me.

00:00:10.780 --> 00:00:12.260
Sorry, sorry.

00:00:12.260 --> 00:00:13.120
I'm Koh Kim.

00:00:13.120 --> 00:00:14.870
I'm part of the Google Play
business development team

00:00:14.870 --> 00:00:15.870
focused on games.

00:00:15.870 --> 00:00:19.750
(IN UNISON): And we're here to
level up your Android game!

00:00:19.750 --> 00:00:20.530
DAN GALPIN: Oh yeah.

00:00:20.530 --> 00:00:22.890
So thank you for joining
us at the very last

00:00:22.890 --> 00:00:24.300
session of the day here.

00:00:24.300 --> 00:00:27.060
We'll hopefully keep you awake
until the big party.

00:00:27.060 --> 00:00:29.350
So we get a lot of
questions, OK?

00:00:29.350 --> 00:00:31.130
And let's go over those first.

00:00:31.130 --> 00:00:31.760
You can hear actually--

00:00:31.760 --> 00:00:35.130
I think they're rehearsing next
door, that loud nose.

00:00:35.130 --> 00:00:36.660
KOH KIM: So how I
get discovered?

00:00:36.660 --> 00:00:37.300
Is one question.

00:00:37.300 --> 00:00:38.870
DAN GALPIN: How do
I get featured?

00:00:38.870 --> 00:00:41.350
KOH KIM: How do I
get five stars?

00:00:41.350 --> 00:00:42.960
DAN GALPIN: How do I get
rid of bad ratings?

00:00:42.960 --> 00:00:45.285
KOH KIM: How do I make
users play my game?

00:00:45.285 --> 00:00:47.470
DAN GALPIN: How do I make
users buy stuff?

00:00:47.470 --> 00:00:50.550
KOH KIM: And that a
lot of questions.

00:00:50.550 --> 00:00:52.330
DAN GALPIN: But sometimes
these questions miss a

00:00:52.330 --> 00:00:53.570
fundamental point.

00:00:53.570 --> 00:00:55.810
And at that point,
in the center of

00:00:55.810 --> 00:00:59.180
everything, there is a user.

00:00:59.180 --> 00:01:00.320
KOH KIM: And we like users.

00:01:00.320 --> 00:01:01.590
I mean, they're fascinating.

00:01:01.590 --> 00:01:01.920
DAN GALPIN: Baffling.

00:01:01.920 --> 00:01:04.450
KOH KIM: They may be quite
baffling creatures.

00:01:04.450 --> 00:01:06.310
DAN GALPIN: So instead of
trying to answer those

00:01:06.310 --> 00:01:09.150
questions up there, we're
focused on what's really

00:01:09.150 --> 00:01:10.952
important, which is that guy.

00:01:10.952 --> 00:01:14.360
KOH KIM: And we'll give you
our not-so-secret formula.

00:01:14.360 --> 00:01:17.410
And it's all about what the
odds are, how do you make

00:01:17.410 --> 00:01:21.500
money, or basically help you
increase the probability of

00:01:21.500 --> 00:01:22.840
getting featured
on Google Play.

00:01:22.840 --> 00:01:23.360
DAN GALPIN: Exactly.

00:01:23.360 --> 00:01:26.030
Happy users, more users--

00:01:26.030 --> 00:01:27.710
that's the way you're ultimately
going to be

00:01:27.710 --> 00:01:28.960
successful.

00:01:30.720 --> 00:01:35.240
So let's start by covering
what you already know.

00:01:35.240 --> 00:01:37.960
OK, last year, we came out
here-- actually Ian and I came

00:01:37.960 --> 00:01:38.770
out here last year.

00:01:38.770 --> 00:01:41.220
And Ian's mysteriously
vanished and

00:01:41.220 --> 00:01:43.230
been replaced by Koh.

00:01:43.230 --> 00:01:43.450
KOH KIM: Sorry.

00:01:43.450 --> 00:01:46.190
He was abducted by aliens, and
they've performed some

00:01:46.190 --> 00:01:50.430
experiments, and out came me.

00:01:50.430 --> 00:01:52.090
DAN GALPIN: And we talked about
something we were very

00:01:52.090 --> 00:01:54.580
excited about, 10 things game
developers should know.

00:01:54.580 --> 00:01:57.940
And the great thing is between
last year and this year, we've

00:01:57.940 --> 00:02:00.260
actually taken those things
and we've codified them.

00:02:00.260 --> 00:02:03.230
We put them up on
developer.android.com.

00:02:03.230 --> 00:02:06.050
In fact, I could stop right
here and just say click

00:02:06.050 --> 00:02:08.759
Distribute and click
App Quality.

00:02:08.759 --> 00:02:09.190
OK?

00:02:09.190 --> 00:02:11.390
It's super, super important,
and here's why.

00:02:11.390 --> 00:02:13.080
Because there's a lot of things
game developers are

00:02:13.080 --> 00:02:16.250
still getting wrong, and this
means that our QA team has to

00:02:16.250 --> 00:02:19.740
spend more time reviewing stuff,
sending cycles back to

00:02:19.740 --> 00:02:21.740
developers, saying, please
change this or

00:02:21.740 --> 00:02:23.140
please change that.

00:02:23.140 --> 00:02:25.480
So an example is navigation.

00:02:25.480 --> 00:02:28.720
We've been telling developers
for years, make sure the Back

00:02:28.720 --> 00:02:29.550
button works.

00:02:29.550 --> 00:02:32.120
Don't put on-screen
prompts on there.

00:02:32.120 --> 00:02:33.780
But people still do it.

00:02:33.780 --> 00:02:35.930
And not only that, if you don't
support the Back button,

00:02:35.930 --> 00:02:37.830
it leads to bad reviews.

00:02:37.830 --> 00:02:38.690
Users say, wait.

00:02:38.690 --> 00:02:40.230
They click, and they
click, and they

00:02:40.230 --> 00:02:41.270
click, and nothing happens.

00:02:41.270 --> 00:02:42.510
They're like, I don't
understand.

00:02:42.510 --> 00:02:44.560
I've been trained by every other
app to do this, and it

00:02:44.560 --> 00:02:45.510
doesn't work.

00:02:45.510 --> 00:02:47.450
And so that's very important.

00:02:47.450 --> 00:02:48.750
There's also other buttons
on the phone.

00:02:48.750 --> 00:02:50.040
Make sure the volume
controls work.

00:02:50.040 --> 00:02:52.840
That's something some
people still miss.

00:02:52.840 --> 00:02:55.930
And also, our QA team really
hates seeing that vestigial

00:02:55.930 --> 00:02:57.630
Menu button there
at the bottom.

00:02:57.630 --> 00:02:59.590
They'll say, no, no,
take it away.

00:02:59.590 --> 00:03:01.380
And it's really, really
easy to take away.

00:03:01.380 --> 00:03:04.010
You just say, I'm going to use
the latest version of Android.

00:03:04.010 --> 00:03:05.560
And that's really cool
for a lot of reasons.

00:03:05.560 --> 00:03:08.390
One, it means you're actually
testing on the latest version

00:03:08.390 --> 00:03:09.370
of Android, which
is really cool.

00:03:09.370 --> 00:03:10.180
We like that.

00:03:10.180 --> 00:03:12.820
And two, it actually means
that that Menu

00:03:12.820 --> 00:03:14.160
button will go away.

00:03:14.160 --> 00:03:15.940
So get rid of it.

00:03:15.940 --> 00:03:18.240
If you really, really want to
have it there, make sure that

00:03:18.240 --> 00:03:19.700
it has a really important
function.

00:03:19.700 --> 00:03:22.160
But you'll still have to explain
to our review team why

00:03:22.160 --> 00:03:25.530
you really need to have
it there in your game.

00:03:25.530 --> 00:03:27.160
All right, so let's go
to our next topic

00:03:27.160 --> 00:03:28.300
everyone gets wrong--

00:03:28.300 --> 00:03:29.000
notifications.

00:03:29.000 --> 00:03:29.760
KOH KIM: Oh, geez.

00:03:29.760 --> 00:03:31.530
DAN GALPIN: Spammy notifications
are really,

00:03:31.530 --> 00:03:32.020
really awful.

00:03:32.020 --> 00:03:33.830
And I'm not even going to put
up an example here, because

00:03:33.830 --> 00:03:34.950
everyone knows this.

00:03:34.950 --> 00:03:37.660
Notifications should not be
something that's an ad for

00:03:37.660 --> 00:03:39.740
something else, OK?

00:03:39.740 --> 00:03:41.100
Notification should be
something that are

00:03:41.100 --> 00:03:42.750
controllable by the user.

00:03:42.750 --> 00:03:44.570
In fact, the best thing you can
do is make it-- if you're

00:03:44.570 --> 00:03:45.740
going to do a lot of
notifications--

00:03:45.740 --> 00:03:47.470
give the user precise control.

00:03:47.470 --> 00:03:48.670
Say, you know what?

00:03:48.670 --> 00:03:50.320
I don't want a notification
between the hours

00:03:50.320 --> 00:03:51.706
that I might be asleep.

00:03:51.706 --> 00:03:53.330
Cool?

00:03:53.330 --> 00:03:56.050
KOH KIM: Or when you're in an
important meeting, or when--

00:03:56.050 --> 00:03:56.460
I don't know--

00:03:56.460 --> 00:03:59.580
sometimes, when you're
on a date.

00:03:59.580 --> 00:04:01.660
When you hear the whole bing--

00:04:01.660 --> 00:04:03.340
DAN GALPIN: Well not, only that,
a lot of notifications

00:04:03.340 --> 00:04:03.716
say, you know what?

00:04:03.716 --> 00:04:05.260
I'm going to play a
custom sound, OK?

00:04:05.260 --> 00:04:07.670
Well, I want my notifications
from things that are really

00:04:07.670 --> 00:04:10.620
important to play sounds, and
from games actually just make

00:04:10.620 --> 00:04:11.970
it a little bit quieter.

00:04:11.970 --> 00:04:13.840
Otherwise, I'm going to turn
them off in the OS, because

00:04:13.840 --> 00:04:15.020
now we allow support for that.

00:04:15.020 --> 00:04:17.740
So it actually helps you
out to do this as well.

00:04:17.740 --> 00:04:19.339
And you'll get bad reviews.

00:04:19.339 --> 00:04:20.220
OK.

00:04:20.220 --> 00:04:22.650
Last year, we talked about all
the things that you shouldn't

00:04:22.650 --> 00:04:24.660
ask for in terms of
permissions, OK?

00:04:24.660 --> 00:04:26.310
You are a game, OK?

00:04:26.310 --> 00:04:29.630
You are not an operating system,
and there's a really,

00:04:29.630 --> 00:04:31.480
really good chance that
you don't need to

00:04:31.480 --> 00:04:33.860
know the user's bookmarks.

00:04:33.860 --> 00:04:36.980
You don't need to know things
like their fine location.

00:04:36.980 --> 00:04:39.260
Unless you are a location-based
game and you

00:04:39.260 --> 00:04:41.040
need to know the user is
standing right here, use

00:04:41.040 --> 00:04:44.130
coarse location.

00:04:44.130 --> 00:04:45.870
You shouldn't actually
have to--

00:04:45.870 --> 00:04:47.965
KOH KIM: Like call
phone number?

00:04:47.965 --> 00:04:48.340
That's kind of creepy.

00:04:48.340 --> 00:04:51.330
DAN GALPIN: You can use Intent
to call phone numbers, OK, if

00:04:51.330 --> 00:04:52.296
you really, really need to.

00:04:52.296 --> 00:04:53.880
You don't need a permission to
actually-- why would you

00:04:53.880 --> 00:04:55.630
directly call them, OK?

00:04:55.630 --> 00:04:56.930
Displaying system
level alerts.

00:04:56.930 --> 00:04:59.390
Unless you absolutely need to
display something on the

00:04:59.390 --> 00:05:00.840
screen when you're not running,
and you have to

00:05:00.840 --> 00:05:03.912
justify that to our review team,
you're never going to

00:05:03.912 --> 00:05:06.420
get featured if you have some
of these bad permissions.

00:05:06.420 --> 00:05:10.230
And then finally, SMS is just
awful, because you can

00:05:10.230 --> 00:05:12.360
actually bill the user for
things without them knowing it

00:05:12.360 --> 00:05:12.860
potentially.

00:05:12.860 --> 00:05:14.280
So don't do it.

00:05:14.280 --> 00:05:17.080
KOH KIM: Who uses SMS
anymore, really?

00:05:17.080 --> 00:05:19.230
I use Hangouts all the
time, perfectly fine.

00:05:19.230 --> 00:05:20.650
DAN GALPIN: Right, exactly.

00:05:20.650 --> 00:05:23.740
We've also talked in the past
a lot about audio, OK?

00:05:23.740 --> 00:05:26.290
Because audio should not play
when the screen is off.

00:05:26.290 --> 00:05:27.960
Audio should not play when
you're on the Home screen.

00:05:27.960 --> 00:05:30.140
Audio should not play when
you're not in the game.

00:05:30.140 --> 00:05:31.015
And this is really bad.

00:05:31.015 --> 00:05:32.840
Because you're in a business
meeting, and suddenly you're

00:05:32.840 --> 00:05:34.060
giving this big presentation.

00:05:34.060 --> 00:05:35.310
You've got your suit
on, so clearly you

00:05:35.310 --> 00:05:36.360
don't work at Google.

00:05:36.360 --> 00:05:39.900
And suddenly, music comes
out of your pants.

00:05:39.900 --> 00:05:42.300
And your boss is like, hey, I
know that he's been playing

00:05:42.300 --> 00:05:44.820
around with some kiddie games
in his spare time.

00:05:44.820 --> 00:05:46.250
So don't do it, OK?

00:05:46.250 --> 00:05:48.050
Our review team will
catch these things.

00:05:48.050 --> 00:05:50.410
We've actually made it
a lot easier to do

00:05:50.410 --> 00:05:51.190
this in Jelly Bean.

00:05:51.190 --> 00:05:53.770
But unfortunately, our review
team will still test on those

00:05:53.770 --> 00:05:56.560
older devices, so you better
make it work everywhere.

00:05:56.560 --> 00:05:59.350
So again, this is a document
that's right online.

00:05:59.350 --> 00:06:02.020
I'm just going through the
document and pointing out

00:06:02.020 --> 00:06:03.110
important things to note.

00:06:03.110 --> 00:06:04.420
StrictMode is cool.

00:06:04.420 --> 00:06:05.340
You should test with it.

00:06:05.340 --> 00:06:07.120
Our testers will test
with it, OK?

00:06:07.120 --> 00:06:09.570
Make sure there aren't big
red flashes conspicuously

00:06:09.570 --> 00:06:10.720
throughout your game, OK?

00:06:10.720 --> 00:06:13.360
It means that there's a chance
that you're causing the UI

00:06:13.360 --> 00:06:14.260
thread to block.

00:06:14.260 --> 00:06:16.050
It means that someone's not
going to be able to hit a

00:06:16.050 --> 00:06:17.880
button and have it be
responsive in the

00:06:17.880 --> 00:06:19.110
middle of your game.

00:06:19.110 --> 00:06:19.940
It sucks.

00:06:19.940 --> 00:06:22.070
You don't want that, OK?

00:06:22.070 --> 00:06:26.360
Finally, your app needs to
provide high-quality graphics

00:06:26.360 --> 00:06:27.820
for different form
factors, OK?

00:06:27.820 --> 00:06:31.110
This is important, because it
turns out that the devices

00:06:31.110 --> 00:06:34.130
that our review team is most
likely to be testing against

00:06:34.130 --> 00:06:35.580
are these guys.

00:06:35.580 --> 00:06:37.560
And they have three different
form factors,

00:06:37.560 --> 00:06:38.660
three different sizes.

00:06:38.660 --> 00:06:40.790
And it turns out if you target
these three sizes, you

00:06:40.790 --> 00:06:44.100
actually are going to get just
about every important device

00:06:44.100 --> 00:06:46.050
that people are spending
money on on Google

00:06:46.050 --> 00:06:47.890
Play in terms of coverage.

00:06:47.890 --> 00:06:50.560
So these are three very
important classes of devices.

00:06:50.560 --> 00:06:53.090
And if you don't have all three
of these, you're going

00:06:53.090 --> 00:06:54.950
to have to explain why your
game can't run on

00:06:54.950 --> 00:06:56.630
all three of them.

00:06:56.630 --> 00:07:00.420
So an example would be
on Nexus 10, OK?

00:07:00.420 --> 00:07:03.160
It is a high-DPI device, OK?

00:07:03.160 --> 00:07:04.840
A lot of older tablets
weren't.

00:07:04.840 --> 00:07:07.970
So if your text is microscopic
and difficult to read and your

00:07:07.970 --> 00:07:11.970
buttons require hands that are
meant for an elf, you probably

00:07:11.970 --> 00:07:16.030
have to go and think about
how you're scaling.

00:07:16.030 --> 00:07:17.030
All right.

00:07:17.030 --> 00:07:19.860
And of course, if you want to
get featured, you better think

00:07:19.860 --> 00:07:22.760
about your assets.

00:07:22.760 --> 00:07:24.410
I'm talking about the
artwork that goes

00:07:24.410 --> 00:07:25.390
along with your game.

00:07:25.390 --> 00:07:27.690
Now we've changed things a
lot in Google Play, OK?

00:07:27.690 --> 00:07:30.180
And we'll go over that in
slightly more detail.

00:07:30.180 --> 00:07:32.300
But the important thing is that
you need to have a really

00:07:32.300 --> 00:07:37.320
great large icon, because icons
are always important.

00:07:37.320 --> 00:07:39.370
They're always the most
important representation of

00:07:39.370 --> 00:07:41.980
your brand within the device
and within Google Play.

00:07:41.980 --> 00:07:44.520
But now they're more important,
because now they're

00:07:44.520 --> 00:07:46.100
the only representation in many

00:07:46.100 --> 00:07:48.370
versions of the Play store.

00:07:48.370 --> 00:07:51.120
So for example, this icon here?

00:07:51.120 --> 00:07:51.640
Great.

00:07:51.640 --> 00:07:53.730
It says, I'm going to be
throwing paper into a bucket.

00:07:53.730 --> 00:07:55.270
I get exactly what's going on.

00:07:55.270 --> 00:07:56.710
It's cool, right?

00:07:56.710 --> 00:07:59.290
And that's the way it
appears on a tablet.

00:07:59.290 --> 00:08:01.155
And you can put a lot of stuff
into these large icons.

00:08:01.155 --> 00:08:01.740
I mean, look.

00:08:01.740 --> 00:08:02.400
I've got a brand.

00:08:02.400 --> 00:08:03.020
I've got a name.

00:08:03.020 --> 00:08:04.580
I know exactly what's
going on here.

00:08:04.580 --> 00:08:06.940
So you actually can get quite
creative with it.

00:08:06.940 --> 00:08:07.940
It's a little different
from what we were

00:08:07.940 --> 00:08:09.620
saying a year ago.

00:08:09.620 --> 00:08:13.110
But the best part about all of
these the guidelines is in

00:08:13.110 --> 00:08:16.290
addition to the guidelines
themselves, we also give you

00:08:16.290 --> 00:08:21.050
an actual test suite that you
can go and hand to your QA.

00:08:21.050 --> 00:08:22.410
Let me just explain.

00:08:22.410 --> 00:08:26.740
It's not just, make sure your
app does this, but it's a set

00:08:26.740 --> 00:08:29.780
of steps to actually go and
verify that your app is really

00:08:29.780 --> 00:08:31.410
doing the right thing.

00:08:31.410 --> 00:08:32.679
Rotate your device this way.

00:08:32.679 --> 00:08:33.549
Click here.

00:08:33.549 --> 00:08:34.610
Click the Home button.

00:08:34.610 --> 00:08:35.659
Check for this state.

00:08:35.659 --> 00:08:37.850
You can actually hand that
to your QA team.

00:08:37.850 --> 00:08:41.230
It is actually what our QA
team does when we look at

00:08:41.230 --> 00:08:44.350
every single featured
application that goes into

00:08:44.350 --> 00:08:45.970
Google Play.

00:08:45.970 --> 00:08:47.440
So remember--

00:08:47.440 --> 00:08:48.920
KOH KIM: So where was
that again, Dan?

00:08:48.920 --> 00:08:50.110
To find everyone.

00:08:50.110 --> 00:08:50.600
DAN GALPIN: Oh, yes.

00:08:50.600 --> 00:08:51.150
That's a good point.

00:08:51.150 --> 00:08:52.770
Here, wait, why don't
you say it?

00:08:52.770 --> 00:08:54.260
It'll have more punch
if you say it.

00:08:54.260 --> 00:08:55.780
KOH KIM: Sure.

00:08:55.780 --> 00:08:57.990
So remember, it's
developer.android.com.

00:08:57.990 --> 00:09:01.310
You go to Distribute and
then App Quality.

00:09:01.310 --> 00:09:02.680
And let me repeat this.

00:09:02.680 --> 00:09:05.470
You should definitely canvass
your QA team or check this,

00:09:05.470 --> 00:09:08.140
because this will definitely
increase your probability that

00:09:08.140 --> 00:09:09.990
our teams will be like, hey,
this is an awesome game.

00:09:09.990 --> 00:09:11.000
We should probably
take a look.

