engines, oftentimes that

00:21:18.260 --> 00:21:20.990
service was actually running
something that wasn't running

00:21:20.990 --> 00:21:22.980
your game engine, so you had
to then provide logic to

00:21:22.980 --> 00:21:24.360
connect everything back.

00:21:24.360 --> 00:21:26.020
And if you were doing
managed items--

00:21:26.020 --> 00:21:27.400
let's say you had a premium
mode of your

00:21:27.400 --> 00:21:28.510
game you were selling--

00:21:28.510 --> 00:21:31.740
then you also had to provide a
database to store all those

00:21:31.740 --> 00:21:32.190
managed items.

00:21:32.190 --> 00:21:34.190
And you probably encrypted that,
because you were trying

00:21:34.190 --> 00:21:36.070
to be really careful about
making sure that people can't

00:21:36.070 --> 00:21:38.420
just easily hack into that.

00:21:38.420 --> 00:21:40.820
And all of these things
are things every

00:21:40.820 --> 00:21:41.990
developer had to do.

00:21:41.990 --> 00:21:44.100
But in Billing v3, we've
actually simplified a lot of

00:21:44.100 --> 00:21:44.620
these things.

00:21:44.620 --> 00:21:48.080
