00:37:21.580 --> 00:37:22.790
Let me explain this quickly.

00:37:22.790 --> 00:37:29.080
So if you're handling analog
axes, and you want to handle

00:37:29.080 --> 00:37:31.220
D-pad events, you actually have
to make sure you handle

00:37:31.220 --> 00:37:33.880
both D-pad events and handle
the hat switch.

00:37:33.880 --> 00:37:36.140
Because what we end up doing
is bundling motion events

00:37:36.140 --> 00:37:38.990
together, and if you say that
you're handling all of them,

00:37:38.990 --> 00:37:41.340
we'll never generate D-pad
events for you anymore.

00:37:41.340 --> 00:37:42.490
Because we're like, oh,
the game's got it.

00:37:42.490 --> 00:37:45.020
We don't need to do those
legacy events for it.

00:37:45.020 --> 00:37:46.750
So if you want to handle D-pad,
you also have to handle

00:37:46.750 --> 00:37:48.080
