in the Linux kernel will

00:38:01.660 --> 00:38:03.580
actually map everything to
Throttle and Brake, no matter

00:38:03.580 --> 00:38:04.600
what the device sends out.

00:38:04.600 --> 00:38:06.740
And as it turns out, the HID
spec mostly sends out

00:38:06.740 --> 00:38:07.710
Throttle and Brake.

00:38:07.710 --> 00:38:10.090
So unless you have an Xbox
controller today with the

